Step 1. Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio.  
• Total Liabilities = Total Liabilities and Owner’s Equity – Total Owner’s Equity  
  = 21,737,442.99 – 16,099,532.29  
  = 5,637,910.70  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner’s Equity  
  = 5,637,910.70 / 16,099,532.29  
  ≈ 0.35  

Step 2. Calculate Net Profit Margin.  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (99,532.29 / 836,813.79) × 100  
  ≈ 11.89%  

Step 3. Calculate Return on Assets (ROA).  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100  
  = (99,532.29 / 21,737,442.99) × 100  
  ≈ 0.46%  

Step 4. Calculate Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio.  
• Since the beginning Accounts Receivable is 0 and the ending is 335,639.38, the average Accounts Receivable = (0 + 335,639.38) / 2  
  = 167,819.69  
• Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Main Business Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
  = 836,813.79 / 167,819.69  
  ≈ 4.99  

Thus, the solution in the requested JSON format is:  

{"solution": {'Debt to Equity Ratio': '0.35', 'Net Profit Margin': '11.89%', 'Return on Assets (ROA)': '0.46%', 'Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio': '4.99'} }
